Thus far, several groups have proposed and experimentally demonstrated
broadband polarization waveplates [12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18]

[12] Ardavan A, 2007 Exploiting the Poincare Bloch symmetry to design high-fidelity broadband composite linear
retarders New J. Phys. 9, 24.
[13] Ivanov S S, Rangelov A A, Vitanov N V, Peters T and Halfmann T, 2012 Highly efficient broadband conversion
of light polarization by composite retarders J. Opt. Soc. Am. A 29, 265.
[14] Peters T, Ivanov S S, Englisch D, Rangelov A A, Vitanov N V and Halfmann T, 2012 Variable ultrabroadband
and narrowband composite polarization retarders Appl. Opt. 51, 7466.
[15] Rangelov A A, 2012 Achromatic change of circular polarization handedness Opt. Commun. 285, 4157.
[16] Rangelov A A and Kyoseva E, 2015 Broadband composite polarization rotator Opt. Commun. 338, 574.
[17] Dimova E S, Ivanov S S, Popkirov G S and Vitanov N V, 2014 Highly efficient broadband polarization
retarders and tunable polarization filters made of composite stacks of ordinary wave plates J. Opt. Soc.
Am. A 31, 952.
[18] Dimova E, Huang W, Popkirov G, Rangelov A and Kyoseva E, 2016 Broadband and ultra-broadband modular
half-wave plates Opt. Commun. 366, 382.


